SYNOPSIS (OPTIONAL)
===================
   #include <idn.h>
   string idna_stringprep(string str, int profile, int flags)

DESCRIPTION
===========
   Prepare the UTF-8 string str(E) according to the stringprep profile(E) (see
   also libidn stringprep(3)).

   profile(E) and flags(E) are one of the values defined in `idn.h`.

   If an error occurs, an exception is thrown.

   The efun is available only if the system supports libidn - in that case 
   __IDNA__ is defined.

HISTORY
=======
   - introduced (3.3.713)

SEE ALSO
========
   convert_charset(E), idna_to_ascii(E), idna_to_unicode(E)
